        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/1–1645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-16">January 16,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. ReDeptel 43, January 15. Plastiras telegram to President and latter’s reply
                    released to press on January 16. Please inform Greek Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
